      "message": "Putvarint doesn\u0027t just encode bytes it encodes them in a way that allows to detect the end of the bytes that make up a single number.\nSee https://golang.org/src/encoding/binary/varint.go#L7\n\nI have lots of integers with fixed number of bytes, this was the easiest way without changing the overall interface.  Settling on a fixed  type (i.e. uint16, unint32 etc.) \nThe TestIntsToBytes would fail with the old scheme because the given number did not fit into two bytes when encoded with Putvarint.",
